    "extras": [
      "Indian passport holders still need a Sri Lanka ETA before arrival; apply online and keep the approval PDF handy because some hotel desks ask for it at check-in.",
      "Show your passport at Sigiriya, Temple of the Tooth and wildlife counters to ask for SAARC pricing; discounts are meaningful and not always volunteered.",
      "Carry LKR cash for cultural-site tickets, buses and tuk-tuks outside Colombo because card machines are patchy in Ella, Sigiriya and Trincomalee.",
      "Book the Kandy–Ella train as early as possible in high season; reserved second class usually sells out first because it balances opening windows with seat certainty.",
      "If your trip is strictly December–March, prioritize Colombo, Kandy, Ella and Galle first; Trincomalee is best added when the east coast turns calm from April to September."
    ],
